From: "Donoghue, Ann" <donogha@HESKA.com>
Date: Fri, 2 May 1997 15:03:25 -0600
Thanks for posting "Tiger Mortality, zoo - China" on Pro/AH. However, I
think the way it was posted may be confusing to readers.
I just got a call from someone at the Univ. of Alberta letting me know
he might have an article that would be useful in solving this 'mystery',
he thought I was the one working on this situation (I'm not).
It's not clear from the post that all I did was take a report in the
published media and then added a couple of quick questions to stir the
imagination.
I guess I intended that this news item become available to the listserve
and if anyone knew anything to help, they could post that to the list as
well, and maybe someone actually working on the case in China would get
the information.
I have no idea who is working on the case, or to whom information should
be sent. I told the fellow who called to please post any information he
may have.
---
Ann
